# Real-Time WebSocket Spec

## Scope

Single WebSocket connection, message registry, delivery modes, subscription keys,
binary media/audio frames, and frontend atom convergence.

## Load when

Changing `internal/ws`, `useWebSocketSync`, live atoms, presence, chat, cursor,
voice/media, notifications, inbox, store/forum/config/page push behavior, or rate
limit/error WS messages.

## Owns

- Backend: `backend/internal/ws/*`
- Frontend: `backend/frontend/src/hooks/useWebSocketSync.ts`
- State: `backend/frontend/src/atoms/{auth,forum,store,inbox,notifications,presence,chat,voice,media,events}.ts`

## Connection Contract

- One singleton WebSocket per browser context.
- URL is `wsBaseUrlAtom` with optional `?token=<JWT>`.
- Text frames are JSON: `{ type: string, payload: JSON|string }`.
- Binary frames are routed to `voice:binary` in the frontend; see
  `voice_chat_architecture.md`.
- Reconnect uses a 3 second timer and replays all tracked subscriptions.
- Auth changes close/reopen the socket; permission-only token pushes patch atoms.

## Delivery Modes

| Mode | Backend API | Use |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Subscription | `Propagate*`, resource keys | Viewed resources such as thread/page/user/inbox conversation |
| Broadcast | `Broadcast`, domain broadcast helpers | Catalog/config/page changes affecting many clients |
| Direct user | `SendToUser`, permission broadcast | Private events: notifications, cart, permissions, purchase outcomes |
| Same-route relay | cursor/audio/media handlers | Presence route-scoped interaction |

