## Atom Convergence

`useWebSocketSync` is the only reducer for WS-pushed shared state. Components may
set atoms from initial REST loads and local optimistic UX, but server-confirmed
shared mutations converge through WS:

`user action => REST mutation => backend => WS push => atom/custom event => render`

## Invariants

- Subscribe on mount/resource load; unsubscribe on unmount.
- Do not poll for entities covered by WS projections.
- Reconnect must replay every active subscription.
- Direct/private messages must be authorized server-side.
- Store cart updates target the owner; catalog updates broadcast.
- Page updates exclude the sender when the HTTP response is already authoritative.
- Slow consumers must not block the hub; use bounded/non-blocking sends where required.

